local Manager = s_WordDictionaryDatabase; Manager.allwords["egalitarianism"]={"egalitarianism","[ɪ,ɡælɪ'teərɪənɪzəm]","[ɪ,gælɪ'tɛrɪənɪzəm]","n.平均主义",'n.平均主义','If we practise egalitarianism -- what we call letting everyone "eat from the same big pot", it will never be possible to raise the people\'s standard of living and stimulate their initiative.','搞平均主义,吃“大锅饭”,人民生活永远改善不了,积极性永远调动不起来。','Men and women who are larger than life *repel us. Our deeply *ingrained *egalitarianism makes us *bridle at the notion that anyone is better than everyone else,” wrote Los Angeles Times columnist Gregory Rodriguez in his story “America needs some heroes, flaws and all”.','那些传奇人物，不分男女都让我们感到反感。我们心中根深蒂固的平等主义让我们对比任何人都强的‘人中杰’观念颇为恼火” 《洛杉矶时报》的专栏作家格利戈里•罗德里奎兹（音译）写道：“美国需要一些英雄、完美的和不完美的都要。”'}
